        "author": "kiwi.eth",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "Is the max amount a validator can be penalized for slashing 1 ETH?",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T02:58:47.399000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "kiwi.eth",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "Seems rather low no? What's the rationale for making it a max of 1 ETH?",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T02:59:45.705000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "protolambda",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "it can get much higher",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:00:03.668000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "protolambda",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "it depends on context; if lots of validators fail at the same time, or coordinate to be bad, they all get slashed extra",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:00:42.311000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "kiwi.eth",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "Where is it in the spec? I just see \n```\n   decrease_balance(state, slashed_index, validator.effective_balance // MIN_SLASHING_PENALTY_QUOTIENT)\n```",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:01:29.326000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "protolambda",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "validators have a withdrawal and exit slowdown. Slashed validators are queued to a lot longer exit. And then half way through that exit, based on the slashings context (the other validators getting slashed), their slashing is completed. See `process_slashings`",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:07:29.356000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "kiwi.eth",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "Ahh so all slashed validators get punished every epoch until they're exited?",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:08:37.093000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "kiwi.eth",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "Oh halfway",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:09:14.658000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "kiwi.eth",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "My bad",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:09:16.877000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
        "author": "protolambda",
        "category": "Consensus R\u0026D",
        "parent": "",
        "content": "only once, exactly half way on their way to the exit. This is to put it into context of other slashings nicely. 50% look back, 50% look forward",
        "created_at": "2020-01-24T03:09:19.414000+00:00",
        "attachments": []
    },
    {
